goals.question: What is the age distribution of the victims?
goals.rationale: This tells us the age range of the victims and if there were any age groups that were disproportionately affected.

goals.question: What is the gender distribution of the victims?
goals.rationale: This tells us if there were any gender disparities in the number of victims.

goals.question: What is the racial distribution of the victims?
goals.rationale: This tells us if there were any racial disparities in the number of victims.

goals.question: What is the distribution of incident types that led to the victims' deaths?
goals.rationale: This tells us the proportion of victims who died due to different types of incidents.

goals.question: What is the geographic distribution of the incidents?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of longitude and latitude
goals.rationale: This tells us the locations where the incidents occurred and if there were any hotspots of violence.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gender'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['death_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['death_date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = race_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Race')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Victims')
    ax.set_title('What is the racial distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['death_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['death_date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    incident_type = data.groupby('type').size()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.pie(incident_type, labels=incident_type.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of incident types that led to the victims\' deaths?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['death_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['death_date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], s=10, alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the geographic distribution of the incidents?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
